 is a media messiah for a secular age. Lofton’s unique approach also situates the Oprah enterprise culturally, illuminating how Winfrey reflects and continues historical patterns of American religions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCelebrities. 0aPopular culturexReligious aspects. 0aReligion and culturezUnited States. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094824240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948242423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520948242/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles